CommonFields.Title: Synthesis and properties of poly(methyl methacrylate)/montmorillonite (PMMA/MMT) nanocomposites
Author: Li, Yan
Zhao, Bin
Xie, Shaobo
Zhang, Shimin
CommonFields.Location: State Key Laboratory of Engineering Plastics, Center for Molecular Science, Institute of Chemistry, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100080, People's Republic of China

Drying-Evaporation.Description: drying and removing the solvent and unpolymerized monomer

MoldingInfo.Description: using a CS-183 MMX Mini Max Moulder (Custom Scientific Instruments)

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: The ultrathin slides were obtained by sectioning the injection-moulded sample along a direction perpendicular to the injection.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: The dynamic temperature spectra of the composites were obtained in three-point blending mode at a constant vibration frequency of 1 Hz, a constant static stress of 2.1 × 105 Pa, temperature range of 25 ∼ 200 ◦C with a heating rate of 5 K min−1 in a nitrogen atmosphere.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Equipment: A Rigaku D/max-RB wide-angle X-ray diffractometer
XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: The operation parameters were Cu-Kα radiation at a generator volt- age of 40kV and current of 100mA. The scanning rate was 8◦ min−1 at an interval of 0.02◦ and the range of the diffraction angle was 2θ = 1.5 ∼15◦.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: scan rate of 20 K min−1 in an atmosphere of nitrogen
